Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3}(chopped into 2cm wide wedges, no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}(to taste), season with @salt{}(to taste) and @pepper{}(to taste). Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, add @korma curry paste{1%sachet} and @yoghurt{75%g} to a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well.

Add the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing used to keep it fresh.

Add the chicken to the pan (reserve the marinade). Cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

Meanwhile, peel and cut the @onion{1}(peeled and cut into 2cm wedges). Add the onion to the leftover marinade and toss to coat.

Once the chicken is browned, pop it onto a lined baking tray.

Place the onion alongside.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until the chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @tomatoes{2}(roughly chopped) and place in a separate bowl.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Halve the @chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped).

Add the sweetcorn and chilli to the bowl with the tomato.

> Use less chilli if you don't like spice.

Halve the @lemon{1}. Squeeze the juice of half the lemon into the bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well, then set aside.

== Raita ==

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Add the coriander and remaining @yoghurt{75%g} to another bowl.

Stir in a squeeze of lemon juice.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, then set the raita aside.

== Final Assembly ==

When everything is nearly ready, place the @naans{2} on a baking tray. Sprinkle with a little @water{} and pop them on the bottom shelf of the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer the cooked chicken to a #chopping board{} and thinly slice.

Share the naans between your plates and top with the tandoori style chicken and onion.

Spoon over the raita and the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet} to finish.

Serve with the potato wedges and sweetcorn salsa alongside.